The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Business Briefs

 New Delhi, Aug. 5: Silver prices spurted to a two-month-high level today with stockists buying, while gold recovered partially on local support. The stockists bought to meet festival demands such as Raksha Bandan and Janmashtmi. The prices scaled a level last seen on June 5 when it traded at Rs 19,200 per kg. Marketmen said silver was much in demand among stockists, which was further fuelled by industrial unit purchases.

 Mumbai, Aug. 5: Century Plyboards India will borrow up to Rs 500 crore from banks and other financial institutions. The shareholders of the company would consider the resolution through a postal ballot, the company informed the Bombay Stock Exchange.

 Mangalore, Aug. 5: The Nagarjuna Power Corporation, which is setting up a 1,105-mw power project in Karnataka at a cost of about Rs 4,300 crore, has secured an in-principle approval from a consortium of financial institutions for loans to the tune of Rs 3,440 crore.

 New Delhi, Aug. 5: TVS Motors has launched a variant of its 125-cc Victor GLX motorbike. The prices start from Rs 42,950. The variant comes with gas filled shock absorbers, new graphics and alloy wheels. It also has an electric start option, a company release said.




